			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>Reuse and Automated Integration of Recommenders for Modelling Languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LissetteAlmonte.html">Lissette Almonte</a>, <a href="../profile/AntonioGarmendía.html">Antonio Garmendía</a>, <a href="../profile/EstherGuerra.html">Esther Guerra</a>, <a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623523">10.1145/3623476.3623523</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagM">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> The core contribution is enabling reuse of recommenders across modelling languages and reducing duplication when integrating them.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper proposes infrastructure to integrate recommenders into modelling tools with less engineering effort.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The setting is modelling languages (DSLs), for which recommendation services are built and reused.
</li></ul></li></ul>
